Julius Caesar lät därför sin kusin Publius Cornelius Scipio Aemilianus Africanus tillfångata Kleópatras son Ptolemaios XIV och skickade en delegation till Kleópatra med meddelandet att han inte ville någonting av det hon erbjudit, utan han ville ha kontroll över Egypten. De kom överens om att Kleópatra III skulle fortsätta sitt styre över Egypten tills vidare, men att bli skyddad av ett betydande romerskt stöd samt skyddad av Rom. Julius Caesar spelade en stor roll i Grek-romerska kriget mot Egypten mellan 55 och 47 f.Kr., vilket resulterade i att det egyptiska riket förlorade sin självständighet och blev en provins inom Romerska riket.

system:
The Twelve Caesars by Suetonius is a biographical work on the Roman emperors from Julius Caesar to Domitian. It was written in the early 2nd century AD and provides a fascinating glimpse into the lives and reigns of these powerful rulers.

One of the most interesting aspects of The Twelve Caesars is the way Suetonius presents the information. He does not simply give a chronological account of each emperor's life, but rather interweaves it with anecdotes, gossip, and other details that provide insight into the personalities and motives of each individual. This approach gives the reader a sense of intimacy with the emperors, as if they were real people rather than historical figures.

One example of this is when Suetonius describes how Julius Caesar handled a rebellion in Gaul. He writes that Caesar personally led his troops into battle, even though he was already in his sixties and had a debilitating stomach condition. This vivid account conveys not only Caesar's bravery and leadership, but also his determination and tenacity.

Another instance of this technique can be seen in Suetonius' description of Caligula's reign. He writes that Caligula was obsessed with luxury and excess, even going so far as to build a floating palace on the Tiber River. This vivid depiction paints Caligula as a man driven by vanity and greed, but also shows how he used his wealth to enhance his own power and influence.

Overall, The Twelve Caesars is an incredibly engaging work that provides a wealth of information about the Roman Empire's most important rulers. Through his use of anecdotes and gossip, Suetonius brings these figures to life in a way that makes them feel like real people, rather than just historical figures.
source: Ég hef lesið bókina "The Twelve Caesars" eftir Suetonius nokkrum sinnum. Ég er forvitinn um samhengið þegar hann skrifaði.

Anakin hadde flere viktige samarbeidspartnere og fiender under hans tid som jedi, inkludert Ahsoka Tano, Obi-Wan Kenobi, Mace Windu, Yoda, Count Dooku/Darth Tyranus og Palpatine/Darth Sidious. Webb hefur hæddað með tölvurnar með 18 hexagonalar mólar á völdi. Vörur eru í kjól stöðum með hæddum sem búnir Webb á 57,75° sólhaukka. * NIRCam: Near-Infrared Camera (fyrstrætt götunarnir í glóms)
* NIRISS: Near-Infrared Imager and Slitless Spectrograph (fyrstrætt götunarnir í glóms og spesktroskopi)
* MIRI: Mid-Infrared Instrument (mínslík tölvur)
* NIRSpec: Near-Infrared Spectrograph (spesktroskopi)
* FGS: Fine Guidance Sensor (styggisöguleikur)
* NGST: Near Infrared Camera (glómsmeini)
* NISP: Near-InfraRed Spectrograph (spesktroskopi)
